result.execSummary:
The defendant Dakota E. Ranney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Defendant shall provide a DNA sample.

Defendant shall undergo counseling as deemed appropriate by probation.    Defendant shall pay supervision fees as ordered by the Department of Corrections. 
If probation is ordered and ultimately revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Dakota E. Ranney in court with attorney Shari L Post.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record.   Victim rights have been complied with.  Plea of no contest to Count 1 in 16CF52 and plea of no contest in 16CF53.  Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court dismisses and read in Counts 2 and 3 in 16CF52 and count 2 in 16CF53.  Court finds defendant guilty of count 1 in 16CF52 and count 1 in 16CF53. Statement by counsel. Statement by defendant.  Court orders in 16CF52 - 2 years prison consisting of 1 year initial confinement and 1 year of extended supervision with conditions of court costs; DNA sample and surcharge and counseling as deemed appropriate by probation.  Sentence concurrent to any sentence defendant is currently serving.   Court orders in 16CF53 - - 6 years prison consisting of 3 years initial confinement and 3 years extended supervision with conditions of court costs; DNA sample and surcharge; counseling as deemed appropriate by probation and restitution joint and several to be determined within 30 days. Sentence is concurrent to 16CF52.    Defendant is eligible for substance abuse program and challenge incarceration program.  District attorney indicated that she will send a memo to the sheriff's department that they should release his phone.   - rt
